README
======

thumble 0.2
    Command-line tool for organizing image files 
    of a directory into an HTML/CSS-based thumbnail
    gallery.

Author:
    Dayo Adewunmi <jargonsummary@gmail.com>

License:
    GNU GPLv3

Requirements:
    - python-imaging (for PIL)
      On Debian: $ aptitude install python-imaging

Installation:
    1. Copy all files into the directory where you store your images
    and run thumble.py in your terminal:
    $ python thumble.py
    2. Open the resulting index.html file in your browser to view
       the thumbnail gallery.

